  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Living Conditions and Access to Basic Items for Protracted Internally Displaced Populations in Camps in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM continues to work in camps to support protracted IDPs in Iraq with camp coordination and camp management activities, site upgrades and maintenance, and the provision/replacement of basic items for those whose items have been damaged, lost or had to be left behind during camp consolidation and closure processes. With a view of an exit strategy, IOM is also increasing its efforts to build the capacity of local actors to respond to and be prepared for displacement and camp coordination as well as camp management.</narrative>
  </description>
